<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-27T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-27T23:00:00-05:00" n="485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.4193/59: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-28T12:00:00+08:00">May 28,
                                1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 28—6:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>221. The British Minister, Sir Alexander Cadogan, has received word that
                            his credentials as Ambassador are being forwarded to him via Siberia.
                            His present plans contemplate trip to Chungkiang [<hi rend="italic">Chungking?</hi>] thence to Nanking arriving there latter part of
                            June at which time he will present his credentials. Pending formal
                            presentation of credentials the status of mission here will remain a
                            legation.</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>